I'm currently using version 0.5.0.M7 and looking at updating to 1.0.0.RC1 but the way active profiles are set has changed.

Previously you were able to add additional active spring profiles through the application-{profile}.yml files.

But now due to the refactoring from ConfigFileApplicationContextInitializer to ConfigFileApplicationListener this no longer works. Calls to add active profiles are now only done after the initial load and not after the profile specific loads.

Essentially I am trying to organise the profiles in such a way that I can specify a single profile on the command line, and that simply activates other profiles (which works brilliantly against 0.5.0.M7).

The following example enables the "a" profile and prints "Service A" when run against 0.5.0.M7 but does not against 1.0.0.RC1 (or snapshot).

Application.java

```
@Configuration
@EnableAutoConfiguration
@ComponentScan
public class Application {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ConfigurableApplicationContext context = new SpringApplicationBuilder(Application.class)
                .profiles("dev")
                .run(args);
        System.out.println(Arrays.asList(context.getEnvironment().getActiveProfiles()));
    }

    @Service
    @Profile("a")
    public static class MyServiceA implements CommandLineRunner {
        public void run(String... args) throws Exception {
            System.out.println("Service A");
        }
    }
}
```

