```

Commit e2c962ac28869512d80054958ab7696e55107eb5 updated several files to use thymeleaf-spring4 (`org.thymeleaf.spring4` package) instead of thymeleaf-spring3 (`org.thymeleaf.spring3` package). However, the [`ErrorMvcAutoConfiguration`](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/blob/43e54d38f7/spring-boot-actuator/src/main/java/org/springframework/boot/actuate/autoconfigure/ErrorMvcAutoConfiguration.java#L121) class in spring-boot-actuator is still checking for the presence of thymeleaf-spring3 on the classpath:

```
if (ClassUtils.isPresent("org.thymeleaf.spring3.SpringTemplateEngine",
        context.getClassLoader())) {
    if (DefaultTemplateResolverConfiguration.templateExists(
            context.getEnvironment(), context.getResourceLoader(), "error")) {
        return ConditionOutcome
                .noMatch("Thymeleaf template found for error view");
    }
}
```

Given that the [`DefaultTemplateResolverConfiguration`](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/blob/43e54d38f7/spring-boot-autoconfigure/src/main/java/org/springframework/boot/autoconfigure/thymeleaf/ThymeleafAutoConfiguration.java#L63) class imports classes from `org.thymeleaf.spring4`, I imagine this should be updated to check for `org.thymeleaf.spring4.SpringTemplateEngine`.

