In order to be able to execute schema.sql / data.sql scripts that contain complex stored procedures we should make the "org.springframework.jdbc.datasource.init.ResourceDatabasePopulator.separator" property customisable, otherwise the `org.springframework.jdbc.datasource.init.ScriptUtils.executeSqlScript(Connection, EncodedResource, boolean, boolean, String, String, String, String)` would get confused by the ";" in the definition of the stored proc itself.

Since this is currently not configurable I had to manually exclude the DataSourceAutoConfiguration via `@EnableAutoConfiguration(exclude = DataSourceAutoConfiguration.class)` and define my own `EmbeddedDatabaseBuilder` with the appropriate separator set.

For reference this was the approach I ended up with:

``` sql
DROP procedure IF EXISTS plus1inout
/;
CREATE procedure plus1inout (IN arg int, OUT res int)  
BEGIN ATOMIC  
    set res = arg + 1; 
END
/;
```

``` java
@Configuration
@ComponentScan
@EnableAutoConfiguration(exclude = DataSourceAutoConfiguration.class)
public class Application {

    @Bean
    public DataSource dataSource() {
        return new EmbeddedDatabaseBuilder().ignoreFailedDrops(true).setSeparator("/;").addDefaultScripts()
                .setType(EmbeddedDatabaseType.HSQL).build();
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(Application.class, args);
    }
}
```

If using custom redis properties in the `application.properties` or yaml equivalent, RedisAutoConfiguration doesn't use these settings when using `RedisPooledConnectionConfiguration.redisConnectionFactory ()`.

```
if (this.properties.getPool() != null) {
    JedisConnectionFactory factory = new JedisConnectionFactory(
            jedisPoolConfig());
    return factory;
}
```

It needs to set the factory config from properties file.

```
if (this.properties.getPool() != null) {
    JedisConnectionFactory factory = new JedisConnectionFactory(
            jedisPoolConfig());
    factory.setHostName(this.properties.getHost());
    factory.setPort(this.properties.getPort());
    if (this.properties.getPassword() != null) {
        factory.setPassword(this.properties.getPassword());
    }                
    return factory;
}
```

Otherwise it uses JedisConnectionFactory defaults which is always localhost and throws connection errors if you're using something other than `localhost`.

