`SpringApplicationContextLoader.processContextConfiguration(ContextConfigurationAttributes)` currently only supports detection of default `@Configuration` classes.

Since `SpringApplicationContextLoader` is a hybrid context loader with support for annotated classes, XML configuration files, and Groovy scripts as _sources_ for the `SpringApplication`, the loader should auto-detect defaults for all supported types just like the core behavior of the Spring TestContext Framework. This should be achievable by making the following (untested) changes.

```
@Override
protected String[] getResourceSuffixes() {
    return new String[] { "-context.xml", "Context.groovy" };
}

@Override
protected String getResourceSuffix() {
    throw new UnsupportedOperationException(
        "SpringApplicationContextLoader does not support the getResourceSuffix() method");
}

@Override
public void processContextConfiguration(ContextConfigurationAttributes configAttributes) {
    super.processContextConfiguration(configAttributes);

    // Neither XML nor Groovy default detected?
    if (!configAttributes.hasResources() && isGenerateDefaultLocations()) {
        Class<?>[] defaultConfigClasses = detectDefaultConfigurationClasses(configAttributes
                .getDeclaringClass());
        configAttributes.setClasses(defaultConfigClasses);
    }
}
